post_cb({"23690099": {"ViewCount": "204", "Body": "<p>I am using the below code to select a random short between 0 and 4000:</p>\n<pre><code>std::random_device rd;\nstd::mt19937 mt(rd());\nstd::uniform_real_distribution&lt;unsigned short&gt; dist(0, 4000);\nunsigned short random_no = dist(mt);\n</code></pre>\n<p>However, I am getting the value 24,583 returned?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "23690146", "Title": "Random number generator min and max-bounded, not working?", "CreationDate": "2014-05-15T23:00:23.107", "Id": "23690099", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2014-05-16T03:12:15.863", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "997112", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><random>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_23690099_23690146_1": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 3487}, "so_23690099_23690146_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "section_id": 3487}, "so_23690099_23690146_2": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 3487}}, "n3337": {"so_23690099_23690146_1": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 3352}, "so_23690099_23690146_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "section_id": 3352}, "so_23690099_23690146_2": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 3352}}, "n4659": {"so_23690099_23690146_1": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 4250}, "so_23690099_23690146_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "section_id": 4250}, "so_23690099_23690146_2": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 4250}}}, "23690146": {"Id": "23690146", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>You'll want to change your code to:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-cpp prettyprint-override\"><code>std::uniform_int_distribution&lt;unsigned short&gt; dist(0, 4000);\n</code></pre>\n<p>The <code>std::uniform_real_distribution</code> you currently use expects to be used with floating point types only.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Now as for the standard because I like to quote!</p>\n<p>In Standard(N3797) 26.5.2 <code>[rand.synopsis]</code> one of the items is the declaration for the <code>std::uniform_real_distribution</code>:</p>\n<pre><code>// 26.5.8.2.2, class template uniform_real_distribution\ntemplate&lt;class RealType = double&gt;\nclass uniform_real_distribution;\n</code></pre>\n<p>which links us to 26.5.8.2.2 for more information, but the important thing is in the declaration already. The templated type is named <code>RealType</code> and under</p>\n<p>Standard 26.5.1.1 <code>rand.req.genl]</code>/1</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_23690099_23690146_0\">Throughout this subclause 26.5, the effect of instantiating a template:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_23690099_23690146_2\">...\n    d) that has a template type parameter named <strong>RealType</strong> is undefined unless the corresponding template\n    argument is cv-unqualified and is one of float, double, or long double.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n</hr>", "LastEditorUserId": "1942027", "LastActivityDate": "2014-05-15T23:20:17.723", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2014-05-15T23:05:46.337", "ParentId": "23690099", "CommentCount": "2", "LastEditDate": "2014-05-15T23:20:17.723", "OwnerUserId": "1942027"}});